# Long-Term Vision

The traditional internet relies on certificate authorities, root trust stores, standards organizations, and governance bodies.

The agent internet will require similar trust anchors.

Authority Nodes provide a decentralized approach to establishing trust without creating centralized control.

They enable ecosystems to coordinate trust while preserving federation.

---

# Conclusion

Authority Nodes establish the highest trust tier within APP and provide the trust anchors required for large-scale autonomous ecosystems while preserving openness, federation, transparency, and decentralization.
